#HOW TO CONNECT YOURSELF WITH GRAPHIC SESSION
#
# 1: Boot the machine
# 2: Fill the username and password fields if required
#		(NOW YOU ARE CONNECTED)
#
#HOW TO CONNECT YOURSELF WITH SSH SESSION
#
# 1: Follow the above mentionned instructions to start the first session
# 2: Open a new terminal window
# 3: Install ssh with the following command : sudo apt install ssh
# 3: Start it with the following command : sudo service ssh start
# 4: Check your ip adress with the following command : ip a | grep "inet"
# 5: Go to the second session and type the following command: ssh user@ipadress
# 6: Type the first session password
# 		(NOW YOU ARE CONNECTED)
